      <h1>About Me</h1>

      <p>
        I am an engineering student interested in computer vision, embedded AI,
        robotics, and physics-informed modeling.
      </p>

      <p>
        My current research focuses on leaf spectral trait inversion. I explore how
        PROSPECT-PRO, neural encoders, VAE structures, and attention mechanisms can
        be combined to estimate plant traits from spectral measurements.
      </p>

      <p>
        I also work on embedded vision systems, including YOLOv8 deployment on RK3588,
        ROS-based perception pipelines, camera streaming, and real-time object
        detection.
      </p>
